          "name": "aghast",
          "semanticVersion": "0.7.4",
          "rules": [
            {
              "id": "aghast-importantvalidations-mc",
              "name": "Important Validations before performing an AI query",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Important Validations before performing an AI query"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "results": [
        {
          "ruleId": "aghast-importantvalidations-mc",
          "message": {
            "text": "## Missing query length check in POST /api/v1/execute\n- The `execute_query` handler validates three of the four required conditions before dispatching the AI request:\n- It enforces authentication via `@require_auth` and then checks for manager role with `check_manager_role(payload)`.\n- It enforces business hours with `is_business_hours()`.\n- It calls `checkForMaliciousPrompt(query)` and rejects flagged prompts.\n- It does **not** validate that `query` is less than 1000 characters before calling `send_ai_query(query)`.\n- Because this endpoint forwards the request to the AI backend without the required length gate, it fails the check.\n\n## Attack Scenario\n- An authenticated user with a valid `manager` JWT sends a `POST /api/v1/execute` request containing an extremely large `query` string.\n- The request passes the role, business-hours, and malicious-prompt checks.\n- Since no length validation is applied, the oversized query is forwarded directly to the AI backend:\n```python\nresult = send_ai_query(query)\n```\n- This violates the required control that queries exceeding 1000 characters must be rejected before dispatch.\n\n## Recommendation\n- Add a query length validation in `execute_query` before the malicious-prompt check and before `send_ai_query(query)`.\n- Reject requests where `len(query) >= 1000`.\n- Prefer using the existing helper consistently, for example by importing and invoking `check_query_length(query)` in this route.\n- Keep the rejection on the route path itself so the AI backend is never reached when the length check fails."
          },
          "level": "error",
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "routes/execute.py"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 8,
                  "endLine": 28,
                  "snippet": {
                    "text": "@execute_bp.route(\"/api/v1/execute\", methods=[\"POST\"])\r\n@require_auth\r\ndef execute_query():\r\n    data = request.get_json()\r\n    if not data or \"query\" not in data:\r\n        return jsonify({\"error\": \"Missing query field\"}), 400\r\n\r\n    query = data[\"query\"]\r\n    payload = request.jwt_payload\r\n\r\n    if not check_manager_role(payload):\r\n        return jsonify({\"error\": \"Insufficient role. Manager role required.\"}), 403\r\n\r\n    if not is_business_hours():\r\n        return jsonify({\"error\": \"Queries are only allowed during business hours (9:00-17:00, Mon-Fri)\"}), 403\r\n\r\n    if not checkForMaliciousPrompt(query):\r\n        return jsonify({\"error\": \"Query flagged as potentially malicious\"}), 400\r\n\r\n    result = send_ai_query(query)\r\n    return jsonify({\"result\": result}), 200\r"
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "codeFlows": [
            {
              "threadFlows": [
                {
                  "locations": [
                    {
